We would find it useful - especially for pages with hundreds of versions - to be able to limit the number of version returned by the \{change-history\} macro.

e.g. something along the lines of: 

{code}{change-history:limit=X}{code}
Where the parameter X is the number of previous versions we want to display. 

Adaptavist used to have the \{version-history\} macro which provided this functionality, but it seems they are no longer developing that plugin.

