This feature would be great when working with 3rd parties on a project that need basic access to view and add content during a project. (ie - basecamp allows you to add as many users as you want, doesn't have to be the case for confluence, but it would be great to at least restrict anonymous users to certain spaces.)

As an admin, share a link to a space that anonymous users can click and access a space. The url should have authentication token in the url. When the anonymous user lands on the space a cookie should be stored in that specific space, allowing the user to access that space only. 

In addition, the user should be able to store their name and email to be used  for commenting, page creation, version tracking, etc.

