As of now, user need to use the method mentioned in our knowledge base article [here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/How+to+Fix+Out+of+Memory+Errors+by+Increasing+Available+Memory] to configure Confluence allocation memory.

It would be better if we provide a feature where users could configure Confluence memory allocation during the installation process using Confluence installer *before* it *start Confluence* so it is not necessary to restart Confluence to applied the new changes.

I recently installed Confluence on Windows and was surprised about the Backup-Path:

{code}
C:\var\www\confluence\backups
{code}

This should be

{code}
C:\Program Files\Atlassian\Application Data\Confluence\backups
{code}

I haven't changed the backup-path, so this is the default setting.

